    "description": "Systematic mesh refinement study conducted on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model. Four mesh densities (coarse, medium, fine, extra-fine) were evaluated for construct stiffness and peak von Mises stress. Richardson extrapolation was applied to estimate the grid convergence index (GCI). The extra-fine mesh (element edge length ≤ 0.25 mm at screw-rod interface) yielded a GCI below 1.2%, satisfying the discretization error acceptance criterion. Solver residuals confirmed below 1e-6 for all load steps.",
